:FED.
Pre-existing illness/injury
:SKRSLUT.
.br
If the insured has a pre-existing illness/injury, this illness/injury must
have been in a good, stable phase for at least two months prior to
departure.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
In this context, 'a good, stable phase'
:SKRSLUT.
.br
is taken to indicate that the condition has been stationary without any
kind of change, development or periodical deterioration that has:
.of 5mm
*¤required contact with a doctor (over and above regular check-ups)
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤resulted in the adjustment of - or plans to adjust - treatment and/or
medication
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤resulted in the scheduling of additional examinations, treatment or
hospitalisation.
.sp 3mm
.of
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
Advance consent
:SKRSLUT.
.br
If the insured has a pre-existing illness/injury, he/she can contact
SOS International prior to departure to request advance consent
stating that coverage under this article still applies despite the
illness/injury. Advance consent from SOS International is binding on
Privatsikring.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Medical advance consent is only necessary if the illness/injury of the
insured is not in a good, stable phase two months prior to departure.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Visit www.sos.eu/mf to take a quick and easy test to establish whether
medical advance assessment is necessary. If you do not have Internet
access, you can contact SOS Travel Service on +45 38 48 82 50.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
5.2 Compensation
:SKRSLUT.
.br
Payment of compensation is conditional upon all treatment and transport
being performed by arrangement with SOS International. As such, it is
SOS International which decides when and how repatriation is to take
place. Therefore, SOS International must always be contacted before any
kind of treatment or transport is initiated.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
5.3 Exceptions
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The insurance does not cover expenses:
.br
.of 5mm
*¤for the treatment of chronic illness or pre-existing conditions if
such conditions deteriorate to an extent that the insured could
reasonably have expected
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for check-ups, treatment or medicine for keeping a chronic illness or
pre-existing condition stable
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for treatment, examination or medication for any kind of mental illness
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤resulting from the insured discontinuing treatment or being rejected for
treatment of a chronic illness or condition
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤relating to treatment needs of which the insured was aware prior to
departure from Denmark
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤attributable to the insured failing to appear at an agreed check-up for
a chronic illness or pre-existing condition
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for medication(s) not prescribed by a doctor
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for treatment and accommodation abroad if the SOS International doctor
has decided - and the attending physician has agreed - that treatment can
be deferred until the insured has returned to Denmark
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for continued treatment and hospitalisation if the insured refuses to
accept repatriation, even though the SOS International doctor has decided
that the insured can be repatriated and the attending physician has
approved the transport
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤attributable to the insured failing to follow the instructions from the
attending physician and/or from the SOS International doctor
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for childbirth or the treatment of illness arising from pregnancy
within one month of the forecast date of birth
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for abortion, unless such is considered a medical necessity to save
the life or health of the insured
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for the replacement or repair of dentures, glasses, contact lenses or
hearing aids
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for recreation or cure breaks
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for treatment or accommodation after repatriation to Denmark or the
insured's country of residence
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for medical evacuation as a result of the insured's fear of infection
.kp off
.kp on
.of 5mm
*¤for plastic surgery or cosmetic operations or the consequences of
